8. What are the values of the following expressions?
'Remember, remember, the fifth of July.'.split()
'-'.join('There can only one.'.split())

Ans:-
By running above expression outpur will be as below .
'There-can-only-one.'
here we are running first string then split that string and then join with (-)

9. What are the methods for right-justifying, left-justifying, and centering a string?
Ans:-
In python we can use rjust() and ljust and center for justify a string , in python as below.

string="           hello"
string.ljust()
string.rjust()
string.center()

10. What is the best way to remove whitespace characters from the start or end?
Ans:-
We can use strip() function in python to remove whitespace charectors from start to end.
as like -
string="this is rajendra pandey      "
string.strip()





